<title>USA: Cinergi sells movie rights to Fox.</title>
<headline>Cinergi sells movie rights to Fox.</headline>
<dateline>SANTA MONICA, Calif. 1997-07-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Cinergi Pictures Entertainment Inc Wednesday said it has agreed to sell its rights in the movie &quot;Die Hard with a Vengeance&quot; to News Corp Ltd unit Twentieth Century Fox Film Corp for $11.25 million in cash.</p>
<p>In a statement, Cinergy said Fox will continue to be responsible for paying residuals on film distribution in territories controlled by Fox.</p>
<p>Cinergi expects its residuals and participation obligations from the movie will not exceed roughly $1.0 million.</p>
